evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a Phase I/II trial (CheckMate 032), Opdivo (nivolumab) treatment resulted in higher objective response rate in small cell lung carcinoma patients with high (21.3%, 10/47) tumor mutational burden (TMB) compared to patients with low (4.8%, 2/42) or medium (6.8%, 3/44) TMB, higher estimated 1-year progression-free survival rate (21.2%, not calculable, 3.1%, respectively), and higher estimated 1-year overall survival rate (35.2%, 22.1%, 26.0%, respectively) (PMID: 29731394; NCT01928394).

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a retrospective analysis, immune-checkpoint inhibitors (Keytruda (pembrolizumab), n=7; Opdivo (nivolumab), n=24; Opdivo (nivolumab) plus Yervoy (ipilimumab), n=21) resulted in significantly improved median progression-free survival (3.3 vs 1.2 mo, HR=0.37, p<0.01) and median overall survival (10.4 vs 2.5 mo, HR=0.38, p<0.01) in small cell lung cancer patients with high tumor mutational burden (TMB>9.68mut/MB) compared to patients with low TMB (TMB less or equal to 9.68mut/MB) (PMID: 30922388).

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a Phase I/II trial (CheckMate 032), Opdivo (nivolumab) and Yervoy (ipilimumab) combination therapy resulted in higher objective response rate in small cell lung cancer patients with high (46.2%, 12/26) tumor mutational burden (TMB) compared to patients with low (22.2%, 6/27) or medium (16.0%, 4/25) TMB, higher estimated 1-year progression-free survival rate (30.0%, 6.2%, 8.0%), and higher estimated 1-year overall survival rate (62.4%, 23.4%, 19.6%) (PMID: 29731394; NCT01928394).

references.title: Tumor Mutational Burden and Efficacy of Nivolumab Monotherapy and in Combination with Ipilimumab in Small-Cell Lung Cancer.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a retrospective analysis, immune-checkpoint inhibitors (Keytruda (pembrolizumab), n=7; Opdivo (nivolumab), n=24; Opdivo (nivolumab) plus Yervoy (ipilimumab), n=21) resulted in significantly improved median progression-free survival (3.3 vs 1.2 mo, HR=0.37, p<0.01) and median overall survival (10.4 vs 2.5 mo, HR=0.38, p<0.01) in small cell lung cancer patients with high tumor mutational burden (TMB>9.68mut/MB) compared to patients with low TMB (TMB less or equal to 9.68mut/MB) (PMID: 30922388).

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a Phase I/II trial (CheckMate 032) that supported FDA approval, Opdivo (nivolumab) as third- or later-line treatment resulted in an objective response rate of 11.9% (13/109, 1 complete response, 12 partial response) in patients with metastatic small cell lung cancer, with a median duration of response of 17.9 months (PMID: 29731394, PMID: 30316010; NCT01928394).

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a Phase I trial, treatment with Roniciclib (BAY 1000394) at the RP2D reduced PCNA expression and resulted in a disease control rate of 17.4% (n=23) in patients with small cell lung cancer (PMID: 28463960; NCT01188252).

references.title: Phase I dose-escalation studies of roniciclib, a pan-cyclin-dependent kinase inhibitor, in advanced malignancies.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a Phase Ib/II trial, first-line treatment with the combination of Roniciclib (BAY1000394) and either carboplatin plus etoposide or cisplatin plus etoposide demonstrated tolerability and resulted in a response rate of 81.4% (35/43; all partial responses), median OS of 12.6 mo, and median PFS of 7.3 mo in extensive disease small cell lung cancer patients; however due to a safety signal in a related trial further development of Roniciclib (BAY1000394) was discontinued (PMID: 30089585; NCT01573338).

references.title: Phase Ib/II study of the pan-cyclin-dependent kinase inhibitor roniciclib in combination with chemotherapy in patients with extensive-disease small-cell lung cancer.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, small-cell lung carcinoma cell lines with overexpression of Trib2 were resistant to cisplatin (PMID: 29312632).

references.title: TRIB2 contributes to cisplatin resistance in small cell lung cancer.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, Talzenna (talazoparib) treatment resulted in reduced tumor growth in small cell lung carcinoma cell line xenograft models with overexpression of SLFN11 and high MGMT, however, to a lesser extent than when compared to the combination of Talzenna (talazoparib) and Temodar (temozolomide) (PMID: 27708213).

references.title: Resistance to PARP inhibitors by SLFN11 inactivation can be overcome by ATR inhibition.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, the combination of Talzenna (talazoparib) and Temodar (temozolomide) resulted in a synergistic effect in small cell lung carcinoma cell line xenograft models with overexpression of SLFN11 and high MGMT, demonstrating a greater reduced tumor growth compared to treatment with Talzenna (talazoparib) alone (PMID: 27708213).

references.title: Resistance to PARP inhibitors by SLFN11 inactivation can be overcome by ATR inhibition.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, Temodar (temozolomide) treatment resulted in reduced tumor growth in small cell lung carcinoma cell line xenograft models with overexpression of SLFN11 and high MGMT, however, to a lesser extent than when compared to the combination of Talzenna (talazoparib) and Temodar (temozolomide) (PMID: 27708213).

references.title: Resistance to PARP inhibitors by SLFN11 inactivation can be overcome by ATR inhibition.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, Talzenna (talazoparib) treatment resulted in minimal anti-tumor activity in small cell lung carcinoma cell line xenograft models with decreased expression of SLFN11 and high MGMT when compared to control (PMID: 27708213).

references.title: Resistance to PARP inhibitors by SLFN11 inactivation can be overcome by ATR inhibition.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, the combination therapy of Talzenna (talazoparib) and Temodar (temozolomide) resulted in no greater benefit compared to Talzenna (talazoparib) treatment alone in small cell lung carcinoma cell line xenograft models with decreased expression of SLFN11 and high MGMT (PMID: 27708213).

references.title: Resistance to PARP inhibitors by SLFN11 inactivation can be overcome by ATR inhibition.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a Phase I trial, Lorvotuzumab Mertansine (IMGN901) demonstrated safety and preliminary efficacy, resulted in a clinical benefit rate of 21.2% (7/33, 1 partial response, 6 stable disease) in patients with NCAM1 (CD56)-positive small cell lung cancer (PMID: 26961907; NCT00346385).

references.title: Phase I study of IMGN901, a CD56-targeting antibody-drug conjugate, in patients with CD56-positive solid tumors.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a retrospective analysis, immune-checkpoint inhibitors (Keytruda (pembrolizumab), n=7; Opdivo (nivolumab), n=24; Opdivo (nivolumab) plus Yervoy (ipilimumab), n=21) resulted in significantly improved median progression-free survival (3.3 vs 1.2 mo, HR=0.37, p<0.01) and median overall survival (10.4 vs 2.5 mo, HR=0.38, p<0.01) in small cell lung cancer patients with high tumor mutational burden (TMB>9.68mut/MB) compared to patients with low TMB (TMB less or equal to 9.68mut/MB) (PMID: 30922388).

references.title: Use of targeted next generation sequencing to characterize tumor mutational burden and efficacy of immune checkpoint inhibition in small cell lung cancer.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a Phase I trial, Poteligeo (mogamulizumab-kpkc) and Opdivo (nivolumab) combination treatment demonstrated acceptable safety, resulted in an objective response rate of 7% (1/15, 1 partial responses) and a disease control rate of 20% (3/15) in immunotherapy-naive patients with advanced or metastatic small cell lung cancer, response occurred regardless of PD-L1, CCR4, CD8 expression levels and tumor mutational burden (PMID: 31455681; NCT02476123).

references.title: A Phase I Study of the Anti-CC Chemokine Receptor 4 Antibody, Mogamulizumab, in Combination with Nivolumab in Patients with Advanced or Metastatic Solid Tumors.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a Phase I/II trial, combination of Lynparza (olaparib) and Temodar (temozolomide) resulted in an objective response rate of 41.7% (20/48) in patients with relapsed small cell lung cancer, with a median progression-free survival of 4.2 months and a median overall survival of 8.5 months, similar response was recapitulated in a coclinical trial with 32 patient-derived xenograft models (PMID: 31416802; NCT02446704).

references.title: Combination Olaparib and Temozolomide in Relapsed Small-Cell Lung Cancer.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, the combination of DT2216 and Venclexta (venetoclax) demonstrated synergy in a small cell lung cancer cell line dependent on BCL-XL and BCL-2 for survival, resulting in decreased cell viability in culture, and led to increased tumor growth inhibition in xenograft models with a mean tumor growth inhibition of 98.2% (PMID: 31792461).

references.title: A selective BCL-XL PROTAC degrader achieves safe and potent antitumor activity.
